<speak version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns:mstts="http://www.w3.org/2001/mstts">
  <voice name="en-US-JennyNeural">
    <prosody rate="0%" pitch="+0st">

  <voice name="en-US-JennyNeural">
    <p>Welcome to our lesson on Mathematics: Linear Algebra for Machine Learning.</p>
    <p>We begin with an introduction to vectors.</p>
    <p>A vector is a mathematical object with both magnitude and direction.</p>
    <p>Its components can be represented in a coordinate system.</p>
    <p>For example, in two dimensions, a vector can be expressed as (x, y).</p>
    <p>Vector addition involves combining two vectors by adding their corresponding components.</p>
    <p>Scalar multiplication involves multiplying each component of a vector by a scalar.</p>
    <break time="400ms"/>
    <p>Next, we explore matrices.</p>
    <p>A matrix is a rectangular array of numbers arranged in rows and columns.</p>
    <p>The dimensions of a matrix are defined by the number of rows and columns it contains.</p>
    <p>Matrix addition is performed by adding corresponding elements of two matrices.</p>
    <p>Matrix multiplication involves taking the dot product of rows and columns.</p>
    <break time="400ms"/>
    <p>Now, let's discuss matrix transformations.</p>
    <p>Matrices can represent linear transformations in space.</p>
    <p>For instance, a rotation matrix can rotate points in a plane, while a scaling matrix can enlarge or shrink them.</p>
    <break time="400ms"/>
    <p>Moving on to the dot product and its applications.</p>
    <p>The dot product of two vectors gives a scalar value and has a geometric interpretation related to the angle between the vectors.</p>
    <p>In machine learning, the dot product is often used to measure similarity between vectors.</p>
    <break time="400ms"/>
    <p>Next, we will cover eigenvalues and eigenvectors.</p>
    <p>Eigenvalues and eigenvectors are fundamental concepts in linear algebra.</p>
    <p>They play a significant role in dimensionality reduction techniques, such as Principal Component Analysis, or PCA.</p>
    <break time="400ms"/>
    <p>Finally, let's look at practical applications in machine learning.</p>
    <p>Linear algebra concepts are essential in algorithms like linear regression and neural networks.</p>
    <p>For example, matrices are used to represent data and weights in a neural network model.</p>
    <p>We can consider a simple case study where we apply these concepts to build a basic machine learning model.</p>
    <p>Thank you for joining this lesson on Linear Algebra for Machine Learning.</p>
  </voice>
    </prosody>
  </voice>
</speak>